WEBVTT

00:00.820 --> 00:02.447
- MARK CYR,
11TH-GRADE ENGLISH.

00:02.480 --> 00:04.755
- YOU KNOW, IN TWO YEARS,
AMBER'S GONNA BE GRADUATED.

00:04.790 --> 00:07.270
I THINK THAT MAYBE THAT'S THE
TIME THAT WE SHOULD GO OUT NEXT.

00:07.310 --> 00:09.244
- WHY ARE YOU
IN THE DOGHOUSE?

00:09.280 --> 00:11.316
- I SHOULDN'T BE MAKING
ANY DECISIONS.

00:11.350 --> 00:12.487
- SMART GUY.

00:12.520 --> 00:13.794
- YOU THINK SO?

00:13.840 --> 00:16.070
I MADE A MISTAKE.

00:16.110 --> 00:17.145
I SLEPT WITH SOMEONE.

00:17.180 --> 00:18.317
- SOMETHING HAS COME UP,

00:18.360 --> 00:20.806
AND I'M NOT GONNA BE ABLE
TO WORK WITH MAX ANYMORE.

00:20.840 --> 00:22.216
- WHAT THE HELL IS WRONG
WITH YOU?

00:22.260 --> 00:24.046
WHY WOULD YOU--
- I KNOW YOU'RE WORRIED

00:24.090 --> 00:25.671
ABOUT LOSING YOUR BABYSI'I'I'ER!
- SHE'S NOT A BABYSI'I'I'ER!

00:25.710 --> 00:27.393
SHE'S A BEHAVIORAL AIDE
FOR YOUR NEPHEW.

00:27.440 --> 00:28.634
HE'S GOT ASPERGER'S!

00:28.680 --> 00:30.079
- I HAVE ASPERGER'S?

00:32.820 --> 00:35.232
WELL, WHAT'S ASPERGER'S?

00:38.210 --> 00:39.711
- WELL...

00:39.760 --> 00:42.342
- [sighs]

00:42.380 --> 00:46.316
- MAX, ASPERGER'S
IS A FORM OF AUTISM.

00:46.350 --> 00:50.241
- WHAT'S AUTISM?

00:50.290 --> 00:53.498
- PEOPLE WHO HAVE AUTISM
ARE CALLED AUTISTIC AND--

00:53.530 --> 00:55.077
- YEP.

00:55.120 --> 00:56.701
BUT SOME PEOPLE
HAVE DISABILITIES, MAX, AND--

00:56.740 --> 00:58.184
- WELL, IT'S NOT REALLY
A DISABILITY.

00:58.230 --> 00:59.561
- IT'S NOT A DISABILITY.

00:59.610 --> 01:00.679
IT'S A SYNDROME.
- IT'S A SYNDROME.

01:00.710 --> 01:03.770
YOUR BRAIN--IT JUST WORKS
A LITTLE BIT DIFFERENTLY

01:03.820 --> 01:05.196
THAN OTHER PEOPLE'S.

01:05.230 --> 01:06.436
- YEAH, IT--YEAH, RIGHT.

01:06.480 --> 01:08.334
- IT JUST--
IT PROCESSES THINGS--

01:08.370 --> 01:10.850
- YOU'RE JUST WIRED
DIFFERENTLY THAN EVERYONE ELSE.

01:10.890 --> 01:12.334
- BUT I DON'T HAVE WIRES
INSIDE OF ME.

01:12.380 --> 01:13.824
- NO, YOU DON'T.
IT'S JUST AN EXPRESSION.

01:13.860 --> 01:16.135
- I HAVE MUSCLES,
AND I HAVE CAPILLARIES,

01:16.170 --> 01:18.650
AND I HAVE NERVE ENDINGS,
AND I HAVE BLOOD,

01:18.690 --> 01:19.509
AND I HAVE BONE.

01:19.560 --> 01:23.417
- YEP, AND THEY
ALL WORK PERFECT LY.

01:23.460 --> 01:26.805
WE JUST ALL HAVE TOUGH STUFF
THAT WE HAVE TO DEAL WITH

01:26.840 --> 01:29.491
IN THIS WORLD,
AND FOR YOU, ASPERGER'S--

01:29.530 --> 01:30.872
IT'S JUST ONE
OF THOSE TOUGH THINGS.

01:30.910 --> 01:32.707
- MM-HMM.

01:32.740 --> 01:34.367
AND NOBODY'S SURE
WHY IT HAPPENS OR--

01:34.400 --> 01:35.799
- AND NO MATTER
HOW TOUGH IT SEEMS,

01:35.850 --> 01:37.602
YOU JUST HAVE TO KNOW
THAT YOUR MOTHER AND I,

01:37.640 --> 01:39.710
WE LOVE YOU--HEY--
AND WE ARE HERE FOR YOU,

01:39.750 --> 01:41.194
AND WE ALWAYS WILL BE.

01:41.230 --> 01:43.266
- ALWAYS.

01:43.310 --> 01:45.369
DO YOU WANT--

01:45.410 --> 01:46.786
DO YOU HAVE
ANY QUESTIONS, HONEY?

01:46.830 --> 01:49.583
OR--

01:49.620 --> 01:51.542
- DO YOU GUYS
HAVE ASPERGER'S?

01:56.660 --> 01:58.901
- UN-UH.

01:58.940 --> 02:01.659
DADDY AND I DON'T HAVE IT.
- DOES HADDIE?

02:01.700 --> 02:05.249
- NO, HADDIE
DOESN'T HAVE IT EITHER.

02:05.290 --> 02:08.259
- JUST ME.

02:11.780 --> 02:14.749
- MAX, WE LOVE YOU
SO MUCH, HONEY...

02:14.780 --> 02:16.224
SO MUCH.

02:16.270 --> 02:17.817
- CAN I GO UP TO MY ROOM NOW?

02:17.860 --> 02:20.613
- SURE, YOU CAN GO AHEAD.
YOU CAN GO UP TO YOUR ROOM.

02:22.970 --> 02:24.414
HONEY, IT'S OKAY.

02:24.450 --> 02:25.542
- NO, JUST STOP.
STOP.

02:25.590 --> 02:27.865
JUST--JUST PLEASE.

02:27.900 --> 02:30.460
- KRISTINA, I'M SORRY.
- I'M NOT MAD AT YOU.

02:30.490 --> 02:33.482
[sobbing]

02:36.460 --> 02:38.280
- HI, MOM.

02:38.330 --> 02:39.877
- HI.
- HI.

02:39.910 --> 02:41.286
- HEY, LOOK AT YOU.

02:41.330 --> 02:42.422
- YEAH?

02:42.470 --> 02:45.598
- YOU LOOK GREAT,
ALL BRIGHT-EYED.

02:45.640 --> 02:48.461
- WELL, I WAS UP ALL NIGHT.

02:48.510 --> 02:50.569
- YOU WERE UP ALL NIGHT?

02:50.610 --> 02:52.919
WRITING, JUST LIKE
WHEN YOU WERE IN HIGH SCHOOL--

02:52.960 --> 02:53.949
MY LITTLE POET.

02:54.000 --> 02:56.639
- OH, YEAH.
- POEMS?

02:56.690 --> 02:58.578
- OH, NO.
- SHORT STORIES?

02:58.620 --> 02:59.826
- UH...

02:59.860 --> 03:01.418
- JOURNAL?
WHAT? WHAT?

03:01.450 --> 03:02.621
- OH, NO.
I DON'T KNOW.

03:02.660 --> 03:04.548
IT'S, UH...

03:04.590 --> 03:05.966
- WHAT?

03:06.010 --> 03:07.147
- I DON'T KNOW.

03:07.180 --> 03:10.308
NOTHING LIKE THIS HAS EVER
HAPPENED BEFORE, YOU KNOW?

03:10.360 --> 03:12.351
IT JUST--

03:12.390 --> 03:15.848
I JUST STARTED, AND IT CAME OUT,
AND I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT IS.

03:15.880 --> 03:17.848
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT IS--
I GUESS A STORY.

03:17.880 --> 03:19.745
IT'S NOT--
I MEAN, IT'S NOT MAGIC.

03:19.780 --> 03:20.849
IT'S JUST A STORY.

03:20.890 --> 03:22.221
- IT SOUNDS GREAT.

03:22.270 --> 03:23.714
- MAYBE.
WE'LL SEE.

03:23.750 --> 03:25.911
- I'D LOVE TO READ IT.

03:25.960 --> 03:27.473
- UH...

03:27.510 --> 03:28.818
- CAN I?

03:28.860 --> 03:31.545
- UM, IT'S NOT IN ORDER,
AND IT DOESN'T FEEL--

03:31.590 --> 03:34.309
I THINK MAYBE I'M NOT READY.

03:34.350 --> 03:35.829
- OH.
OH, WELL...

03:35.870 --> 03:38.725
- BUT I'LL LET YOU KNOW.
- OKAY.

03:38.770 --> 03:39.998
- WHEN I AM,
YOU'LL BE THE--

03:40.040 --> 03:41.553
YOU KNOW,
ONE OF THE FIRST TO--

03:41.600 --> 03:43.386
BYE.

03:43.430 --> 03:46.661
[door closes]

03:46.700 --> 03:48.395
- [chuckles]

03:48.430 --> 03:51.945
- SEE YOU LATER.

03:51.990 --> 03:54.561
UH-UH.
GET AWAY.

03:54.610 --> 03:56.293
- SWEETIE, CAN--
CAN WE TALK FOR ONE SECOND?

03:56.330 --> 03:57.809
- NO. NO.
- JUST GIVE ME--

03:57.850 --> 03:59.715
I JUST WANT ONE MINUTE, OKAY?

03:59.750 --> 04:00.853
- GET AWAY. MOVE.
- HOLD ON.

04:00.890 --> 04:03.814
WILL YOU PLEASE JUST--
- GET OFF--GET OFF THE DOOR!

04:03.860 --> 04:06.442
- SWEETIE!

04:08.520 --> 04:11.489
[A Fine Frenzy's
Electric Twist]

04:21.810 --> 04:25.086
- YOU SHOULD BE WILDER

04:25.120 --> 04:28.669
YOU'RE NO FUN AT ALL

04:28.710 --> 04:30.678
YEAH, THANKS FOR THE INPUT

04:30.710 --> 04:31.677
- OH, GOD.
OH, MY GOD.

04:31.710 --> 04:33.746
NO, NO, NO, NO.
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

04:33.790 --> 04:35.405
OH, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

04:35.440 --> 04:37.544
- DID YOU LOSE SOMETHING?
- OH, MY GOD. HI.

04:37.580 --> 04:39.377
- HI.

04:39.410 --> 04:42.652
UH, I-IS THIS YOUR TECHNIQUE
FOR BREAKING IN?

04:42.690 --> 04:43.793
'CAUSE I'M
A LITTLE DISAPPOINTED.

04:43.830 --> 04:44.967
- IT'S NOT WHAT YOU THINK.

04:45.000 --> 04:46.171
- WELL, I'M--
I'M JUST GUESSING.

04:46.210 --> 04:49.008
IT'S NOT OFTEN I FIND WOMEN
KNEELING OUTSIDE MY DOOR.

04:49.040 --> 04:51.031
THIS IS KIND OF
A "DEAR DIARY" DAY FOR ME.

04:51.080 --> 04:52.172
- LISTEN, LOOK,

04:52.220 --> 04:54.313
FOR THE RECORD, I WAS TRYING
TO GET SOMETHING BACK,

04:54.360 --> 04:56.009
OKAY, THAT I PUT UNDER THERE.

04:56.050 --> 04:58.848
SO THIS IS NOT, LIKE, STEALING
OR SNOOPING OR ANYTHING.

04:58.880 --> 05:01.678
- NO, NO.
Y-YOU'RE JUST BLUSHING.

05:01.710 --> 05:03.849
- [laughs]

05:03.880 --> 05:05.677
OH, MY GOD.

05:05.710 --> 05:06.677
HI.

05:06.720 --> 05:08.574
- HI.

05:08.610 --> 05:11.647
UM...

05:11.690 --> 05:13.021
I'M JUST GONNA GET
INTO MY APARTMENT.

05:13.070 --> 05:14.856
- OH, THIS IS YOUR APARTMENT?

05:14.900 --> 05:16.447
- OH, YEAH. YEAH.
- OH.

05:16.480 --> 05:17.686
THAT'S SO--

05:17.730 --> 05:18.822
- SUCH A COINCIDENCE.

05:18.870 --> 05:21.896
- I'LL JUST TAKE THAT,
AND I'LL, UH, SEE YOU LATER.

05:21.940 --> 05:23.896
- YOU'RE NOT--YOU'RE NOT
GONNA TELL ME WHAT IT IS?

05:23.940 --> 05:25.999
- OH, NO, NO.
- WAY TO AMP UP THE MYSTERY.

05:26.040 --> 05:27.837
I'LL JUST NEVER KNOW WHY I SAW

05:27.870 --> 05:29.872
SARAH BRAVERMAN
KNEELING OUTSIDE MY DOOR.

05:29.910 --> 05:31.901
- FINE.
OKAY.

05:31.950 --> 05:33.906
UM...
I JUST--

05:33.950 --> 05:36.157
I WROTE THIS THING,
AND I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT IS.

05:36.190 --> 05:38.636
IT JUST KIND OF CAME OUT OF ME,
AND I DIDN'T SLEEP,

05:38.680 --> 05:41.467
AND IT FELT REALLY GREAT,
AND THEN I WAS SEIZED

05:41.510 --> 05:44.673
WITH THIS IDEA THAT I-I-I WANTED
SOMEONE TO READ IT,

05:44.720 --> 05:47.371
AND I THOUGHT OF YOU.

05:47.410 --> 05:48.820
- OH.

05:48.860 --> 05:50.373
- AND THEN WHEN I PUT IT
UNDER YOUR DOOR,

05:50.410 --> 05:51.991
THE FEELING OF WANTING
SOMEONE TO READ IT

05:52.040 --> 05:53.860
WAS IMMEDIATELY REPLACED
BY INTENSE REGRET

05:53.900 --> 05:55.447
AND DEEP, DEEP SHAME.

05:55.490 --> 05:56.934
UM, SO THAT'S THE STORY,

05:56.970 --> 05:58.790
AND NOW I'LL JUST LET YOU GO
ABOUT YOUR DAY.

05:58.840 --> 06:00.171
- I WOULD LOVE TO READ IT.
- WHAT?

06:00.220 --> 06:01.551
- I-I-I'D LOVE TO READ IT.

06:01.600 --> 06:02.931
I'D BE HONORED.

06:02.980 --> 06:05.631
- [sighs]
ARE--REALLY?

06:05.670 --> 06:06.898
- YEAH, ABSOLUTELY.

06:06.950 --> 06:07.803
- ARE YOU SURE?
- I'M SURE.

06:07.850 --> 06:09.568
- I MEAN--NO.
IT'S, LIKE, I WROTE IT,

06:09.610 --> 06:11.805
SO CHANCES ARE--WHOO!
SM ELLY.

06:11.850 --> 06:14.080
- YEAH, I'M SURE. I KNOW.
EVERYTHING YOU DO IS TERRIBLE.

06:14.130 --> 06:15.950
CAN I--CAN I READ IT?

06:15.990 --> 06:17.878
- UM, YES.

06:17.920 --> 06:19.956
YES, YOU CAN.
- THANK YOU.

06:20.000 --> 06:23.822
- I, UH--I THINK--
YEAH, I THINK THIS IS GOOD.

06:23.860 --> 06:25.657
THIS IS REALLY WONDERFUL.
THANK YOU.

06:25.690 --> 06:27.419
FANTASTIC.
- ANYTIME.

06:27.450 --> 06:28.758
IT IS FANTASTIC.

06:28.800 --> 06:30.449
AND IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU.

06:30.490 --> 06:33.618
- IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU.

06:33.660 --> 06:38.040
- ALL RIGHT...
I'LL GET STARTED RIGHT AWAY.

06:38.080 --> 06:40.799
ALL RIGHT, BYE.
- BYE.

06:43.230 --> 06:46.017
- MAY GOD BLESS
AND KEEP YOU ALWAYS

06:46.060 --> 06:48.676
AND MAY YOUR WISHES
ALL COME TRUE

06:48.710 --> 06:51.019
MAY YOU ALWAYS DO
FOR OTHERS

06:51.060 --> 06:53.233
AND LET OTHERS DO FOR YOU

06:53.270 --> 06:56.023
MAY YOU BUILD A LADDER
TO THE STARS

06:56.070 --> 06:58.061
AND CLIMB ON EVERY RUNG

06:58.100 --> 07:00.614
AND MAY YOU STAY

07:00.660 --> 07:02.924
FOREVER YOUNG

07:02.970 --> 07:05.791
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE RIGHTEOUS

07:05.830 --> 07:08.037
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE TRUE

07:08.080 --> 07:10.548
MAY YOU ALWAYS KNOW
THE TRUTH

07:10.600 --> 07:12.761
AND SEE THE LIGHTS
SURROUNDING YOU

07:12.810 --> 07:15.563
MAY YOU ALWAYS BE
COURAGEOUS

07:15.600 --> 07:17.739
STAND UPRIGHT
AND BE STRONG

07:17.780 --> 07:19.668
AND MAY YOU STAY

07:19.710 --> 07:22.190
FOREVER YOUNG

07:22.230 --> 07:24.642
MAY YOU STAY

07:24.680 --> 07:28.025
FOREVER YOUNG

07:31.000 --> 07:32.137
- SO...

07:32.170 --> 07:36.482
YOU CALLED IT
A "DISABILITY"?

07:36.520 --> 07:37.726
- YEAH.

07:37.760 --> 07:40.240
LOOK, I'M SURE THAT THAT'S NOT
WHAT I WAS SUPPOSED TO DO,

07:40.280 --> 07:41.963
BUT I WAS CAUGHT
COMPLETELY OFF GUARD.

07:42.010 --> 07:44.626
MAX JUST OVERHEARD MY BROTHER
AND I SHOUTING AT EACH OTHER.

07:44.670 --> 07:46.524
HE'S STANDING THERE
IN THE STAIRCASE.

07:46.560 --> 07:47.629
YOU KNOW, THE RIGHT WORDS

07:47.670 --> 07:49.012
WEREN'T EXACTLY
ROLLING OFF MY TONGUE.

07:49.050 --> 07:50.870
- I DON'T MEAN TO SOUND
JUDGMENTAL.

07:50.910 --> 07:52.707
I JUST WANT TO UNDERSTAND
WHAT MAX HEARD.

07:52.740 --> 07:54.776
- WHO KNOWS WHAT HE HEARS?

07:54.810 --> 07:58.769
- WHAT ELSE
DID YOU SAY TO HIM?

07:58.820 --> 08:01.948
- I SAID THAT HE
WAS WIRED DIFFERENTLY.

08:01.990 --> 08:03.127
YOU KNOW?

08:03.170 --> 08:05.024
I TOLD HIM WE LOVED HIM,
AND I KNEW

08:05.070 --> 08:06.298
THAT IT WAS A TOUGH SITUATION.

08:06.340 --> 08:07.967
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU SUPPOSED
TO SAY TO HIM?

08:08.000 --> 08:11.106
- WELL, YOU WANT
TO BE SIMPLE,

08:11.140 --> 08:13.893
DESCRIPTIVE, UPBEAT.

08:13.940 --> 08:17.216
EMPHASIZE SOME POSITIVE ASPECTS
OF HAVING ASPERGER'S.

08:17.250 --> 08:19.593
- OH, YEAH, THE POSITIVE ASPECTS
OF ASPERGER'S.

08:19.630 --> 08:21.143
I'M SORRY THOSE WEREN'T
OCCURRING TO ME IN THE MOMENT.

08:21.190 --> 08:23.943
I MEAN, IS THIS SERIOUSLY
YOUR ADVICE--TO BE UPBEAT?

08:23.980 --> 08:25.732
- IT'S A SUGGESTION
THAT I BELIEVE HELPS, YES.

08:25.780 --> 08:27.873
- WELL, I'M SORRY.
IT WAS AN EMOTIONAL SITUATION.

08:27.920 --> 08:29.296
I WAS DOING THE BEST I COULD.
- I UNDERSTAND.

08:29.330 --> 08:30.604
- I MEAN, KRISTINA WAS CRYING.
IT WAS LATE.

08:30.640 --> 08:31.436
I'D JUST FINISHED...
- WAIT A MINUTE.

08:31.470 --> 08:32.812
- SHOUTING
THAT HE HAD ASPERGER'S.

08:32.850 --> 08:34.124
I DIDN'T KNOW HE WAS THERE.

08:34.160 --> 08:36.219
- KRISTINA, YOU CRIED?

08:36.270 --> 08:38.613
- YEAH.

08:38.650 --> 08:41.062
I CRIED.

08:41.100 --> 08:42.783
- WAIT A MINUTE.
- I CRIED.

08:42.830 --> 08:44.138
- ARE YOU REALLY GETTING
JUDGMENTAL

08:44.170 --> 08:45.649
BECAUSE SHE WAS FEELING
EMOTIONAL?

08:45.690 --> 08:47.100
- IT'S OKAY, HONEY.
- NO, OF COURSE NOT.

08:47.140 --> 08:48.653
IT'S COMPLETELY NATURAL.

08:48.700 --> 08:50.144
I PROMISE YOU
I'M NOT BEING JUDGMENTAL.

08:50.180 --> 08:52.978
I-I'M LOOKING FOR SOMETHING
THAT I THINK WILL HELP.

08:53.010 --> 08:55.114
- ARE YOU SAYING
THAT I SHOULDN'T HAVE CRIED?

08:55.150 --> 08:57.186
I MEAN,
I DIDN'T REALLY PLAN ON IT.

08:57.220 --> 08:58.664
- CRYING IMPLIES
THAT HAVING ASPERGER'S

08:58.710 --> 09:00.803
IS SOMETHING TO MOURN, RIGHT?

09:00.850 --> 09:03.739
WE WANT TO BE SENDING A MESSAGE
THAT MAX IS LIKE EVERYONE ELSE.

09:03.780 --> 09:06.749
HE HAS HIS STRENGTHS.
HE HAS HIS CHALLENGES.

09:06.780 --> 09:08.122
ASPERGER'S
IS A PART OF THAT.

09:08.160 --> 09:09.912
- OKAY, GREAT.
ALL RIGHT, WELL, SHE CRIED.

09:09.960 --> 09:11.746
I CALLED IT A "DISABILITY."
WE BLEW IT.

09:11.790 --> 09:13.951
I THINK THAT'S CLEAR.
SO WHAT DO WE DO NOW?

09:14.000 --> 09:17.163
- WELL, I'M NOT SURE.

09:17.210 --> 09:19.849
- [sighs]

09:19.900 --> 09:21.686
I MEAN,
YOU GOT TO BE JOKING!

09:21.730 --> 09:23.618
I MEAN, ARE YOU--SERIOUSLY,
THIS IS YOUR ADVICE?

09:23.660 --> 09:25.002
I MEAN,
ARE WE THE ONLY PARENTS

09:25.040 --> 09:26.655
TO HAVE EVER SCREWED UP
THIS BADLY?

09:26.700 --> 09:29.931
- I THINK YOU SHOULD TRY
FOR A REDO WITH MAX.

09:29.980 --> 09:32.323
- WHAT IS THIS?

09:32.360 --> 09:34.089
- THAT IS A SCRIPT.

09:34.120 --> 09:36.259
IT'S A BLUEPRINT FOR YOU
TO TALK TO YOUR CHILD

09:36.290 --> 09:38.702
ABOUT THIS DIAGNOSIS.

09:38.750 --> 09:40.911
SO YOU SHOULD READ
IT TOGETHER,

09:40.950 --> 09:43.646
MAINLY BECAUSE I THINK YOU BOTH
NEED TO BE ON THE SAME PAGE

09:43.680 --> 09:47.684
BEFORE YOU TALK TO MAX
ABOUT HIS AUTISM AGAIN.

09:47.720 --> 09:50.609
SO TAKE SOME TIME.
TAKE A FEW DAYS.

09:50.650 --> 09:51.719
REALLY STUDY IT.

09:51.760 --> 09:54.684
PRACTICE.

09:54.730 --> 09:56.686
- PRACTICE.

09:56.730 --> 09:59.142
- I KNOW YOU BOTH WANT
THE BEST FOR MAX. I DO TOO.

09:59.180 --> 10:03.048
THIS IS AN IMPORTANT
TRANSITION FOR HIM.

10:03.080 --> 10:07.699
HE'S GOING TO NEED YOU.

10:07.740 --> 10:10.220
- I JUST FEEL LIKE YOU'RE NOT
ON BOARD WITH THIS AT ALL.

10:10.260 --> 10:11.875
- YOU'RE DAMN RIGHT I'M NOT
ON BOARD, HONEY.

10:11.920 --> 10:13.182
I MEAN, WE GO TO HIM FOR HELP,

10:13.230 --> 10:16.017
AND HIS ADVICE IS TO FEED OUR
SON A BUNCH OF POSITIVE SPIN.

10:16.060 --> 10:17.641
- MM-HMM. THAT'S NOT
WHAT HE MEANT AT ALL.

10:17.680 --> 10:18.817
- THAT IS WHAT HE MEANT.

10:18.850 --> 10:20.294
LET'S LOOK
AT THE SCRIPT TOGETHER.

10:20.340 --> 10:22.058
LET'S BREAK IT DOWN.
GO AHEAD.

10:22.100 --> 10:23.749
- "QUALITIES AND DIFFICULTIES
OF THOSE WITH ASPERGER'S.

10:23.790 --> 10:25.200
QUALITY--DETERMINED."

10:25.240 --> 10:27.060
THAT'S A POSITIVE THING.
- ALL RIGHT.

10:27.100 --> 10:30.137
- "DIFFICULTY--MAKING FRIENDS."
- MM-HMM.

10:30.180 --> 10:32.694
- "QUALITY--
HUMOROUS IN A UNIQUE WAY."

10:32.730 --> 10:34.209
- MEANING NO ONE GETS
HIS JOKES.

10:34.250 --> 10:37.731
- "QUALITY--EXCEPTIONAL
AT REMEMBERING THINGS

10:37.770 --> 10:39.180
THAT OTHERS CAN'T."

10:39.220 --> 10:41.666
- THINGS THAT OTHER PEOPLE
DON'T CARE ABOUT--BUGS.

10:41.710 --> 10:43.189
THE LIFE SPAN
OF A PARTICULAR INSECT

10:43.220 --> 10:45.188
OR THE WINGSPAN
OF A FLYING COCKROACH.

10:45.230 --> 10:46.356
WHO CARES?

10:46.400 --> 10:47.913
- THAT'S WHAT THAT MEANS.
- I CA--I CARE.

10:47.950 --> 10:51.738
"DIFFICU LTY--READING
OTHER PEOPLE'S CUES."

10:51.780 --> 10:53.259
I THINK THIS IS A GOOD START.

10:53.300 --> 10:55.439
THIS IS HELPFUL.
- WELL, I DON'T.

10:55.480 --> 10:57.687
I THINK IT'S A BUNCH
OF POSITIVE LANGUAGE.

10:57.720 --> 10:59.028
THAT'S ALL IT IS.

10:59.070 --> 11:01.686
IT'S A LIE.

11:01.730 --> 11:03.686
- [sighs]

11:03.730 --> 11:06.346
- CAN I BRING
MY DRESS-UP CLOTHES

11:06.380 --> 11:08.689
TO THE SLEEPOVER
WITH JABBAR?

11:08.730 --> 11:10.482
- UM...

11:10.530 --> 11:13.499
GOSH, SWEETIE, I DON'T KNOW
IF WE'RE GONNA BE ABLE

11:13.530 --> 11:15.384
TO HAVE THAT SLEEPOVER
WITH JABBAR.

11:15.430 --> 11:17.489
- NO, NO, NO, NO. YOU GUYS SAID
THAT YOU WERE HAVING

11:17.530 --> 11:20.704
AN ANNIVERSARY FOR LOVE,
AND THAT MEANT

11:20.740 --> 11:22.367
THAT I GOT TO HAVE
A SLEEPOVER.

11:22.400 --> 11:23.981
- I KNOW THAT'S
WHAT I SAID, SWEETIE, AND...

11:24.020 --> 11:25.328
- SYD, HEAD UPSTAIRS.
- I MEANT IT.

11:25.370 --> 11:27.361
- GET YOUR SHOES ON.
FIND YOUR BACKPACK.

11:27.410 --> 11:29.196
WE'LL FIGURE OUT ALL
THE SLEEPOVER DETAILS LATER.

11:29.240 --> 11:30.468
OKAY?
- OKAY.

11:30.510 --> 11:32.922
BUT I REALLY, REALLY WANT
TO HAVE A SLEEPOVER.

11:32.960 --> 11:34.757
- OKAY, SO DO WE.

11:34.790 --> 11:36.724
- WE REALLY DO.
WE DO, SWEETIE.

11:36.760 --> 11:38.239
I PROMISE.

11:38.280 --> 11:40.339
- THE ONE TIME
WE'RE ABLE TO ACTUALLY HAVE

11:40.380 --> 11:43.315
AN ANNIVERSARY DATE,
JUST US, THE ONE TIME--

11:43.350 --> 11:45.079
- I KNOW, BABE.
I KNOW.

11:45.110 --> 11:47.169
- BUT IF WE CANCEL WITH HER,
WON'T IT LOOK

11:47.220 --> 11:49.074
LIKE WE'RE TAKING CROSBY'S SIDE
IN THE WHOLE THING?

11:49.120 --> 11:50.382
- WILL IT?
- IT MIGHT.

11:50.430 --> 11:52.011
- I DON'T WANT TO TAKE SIDES.

11:52.050 --> 11:53.847
HE'S MY BROTHER,
BUT HE'S SCREWED UP.

11:53.880 --> 11:56.292
- IS THAT AN UNDERSTATEMENT,
OR ARE YOU JUST BEING LITERAL?

11:56.330 --> 11:57.877
HMM.

11:57.920 --> 11:59.808
- OKAY,
WE SHOULD CANCEL, RIGHT?

11:59.850 --> 12:02.023
- YEP.
- YES.

12:02.060 --> 12:03.436
OKAY.

12:03.480 --> 12:05.471
HERE WE GO.
- [sighs]

12:05.510 --> 12:08.445
[phone beeps, dial tone]

12:08.480 --> 12:10.960
- I MEAN, WHAT DO YOU
EVEN SAY?

12:11.000 --> 12:12.513
- "SORRY ABOUT YOUR BETRAYAL."

12:12.550 --> 12:14.347
[both chuckle]

12:14.380 --> 12:16.792
- THAT'S TERRIBLE.
- SORRY. I'M JUST--

12:16.830 --> 12:18.764
I WAS REALLY LOOKING FORWARD
TO TAKING YOU OUT

12:18.800 --> 12:20.279
ON AN ANNIVERSARY DATE, HONEY.

12:20.320 --> 12:21.423
EIGHT YEARS.

12:21.460 --> 12:23.519
- I KNOW.

12:23.570 --> 12:25.185
I KNOW.

12:31.610 --> 12:33.009
- MAX?

12:33.060 --> 12:35.460
- MM-HMM?

12:35.510 --> 12:37.853
- BUDDY?
- WHAT?

12:37.890 --> 12:41.303
- IS THERE ANYTHING
YOU WANT TO TALK ABOUT?

12:41.340 --> 12:42.853
- NOPE.

12:42.900 --> 12:45.300
- ARE YOU SURE?

12:45.350 --> 12:47.136
- YEP.

12:47.180 --> 12:48.511
- HEY.
- OKAY.

12:48.560 --> 12:50.414
- MORNING, EVERYBODY.

12:50.450 --> 12:53.556
- HEY.

12:53.600 --> 12:56.489
- YOU ALL RIGHT?

12:56.530 --> 12:59.567
- I DON'T KNOW.

12:59.600 --> 13:02.012
- ALL RIGHT, LISTEN, HEY, MAX,
I GOT TO TAKE OFF TO WORK.

13:02.050 --> 13:03.460
YOU HAVE A GOOD DAY,
OKAY, BUDDY?

13:03.500 --> 13:04.842
- OKAY.
- HONEY, COME ON.

13:04.880 --> 13:07.053
- I'LL BE RIGHT BACK, BUDDY.

13:09.060 --> 13:10.846
- LOOK, WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?
HE LOOKS FINE.

13:10.890 --> 13:12.539
- HE LOOKS
HOW HE ALWAYS LOOKS.

13:12.580 --> 13:14.855
I JUST THINK THAT MAYBE
WE SHOULD BRING THIS UP AGAIN

13:14.890 --> 13:16.198
AND GIVE HIM THE CHANCE
TO TALK ABOUT IT.

13:16.240 --> 13:17.377
- I DON'T WANT TO UPSET HIM.

13:17.410 --> 13:18.479
HE'S PROCESSING IT
IN HIS OWN WAY.

13:18.520 --> 13:20.545
I'M NOT INTERESTED
IN MEMORIZING A BUNCH OF FACTS

13:20.590 --> 13:22.171
THAT HAVE BEEN POLISHED UP
TO MAKE IT SOUND

13:22.210 --> 13:23.063
LIKE HE'S WON SOMETHING.

13:23.110 --> 13:24.554
- I'M NOT SAYING
THAT WE SHOULD DO THAT.

13:24.590 --> 13:26.205
I'M SAYING THAT
WE SHOULD JUST TALK TO HIM.

13:26.250 --> 13:27.558
- LOOK, I GOT TO GO
TO WORK, OKAY?

13:27.590 --> 13:29.558
CAN WE TALK
ABOUT THIS LATER, PLEASE?

13:29.600 --> 13:31.044
- YEAH.
- I LOVE YOU.

13:31.080 --> 13:33.071
- [scoffs]

13:39.470 --> 13:42.018
[sighs]

13:42.060 --> 13:43.436
BUDDY?

13:43.470 --> 13:46.849
- I FEEL LIKE
IF I COULD, YOU KNOW,

13:46.890 --> 13:49.859
GET HER TO TALK TO ME...

13:49.890 --> 13:53.018
OR GET HER TO LOOK AT ME
AND THEN TALK TO ME...

13:53.070 --> 13:55.300
- THIS IS THE PLAN?
- I COULD MAYBE MAKE IT RIGHT.

13:55.350 --> 13:57.136
W-WHAT DO YOU THINK?

13:57.180 --> 13:59.967
- I-I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT TO SAY.

14:00.010 --> 14:02.035
- NOBODY KNOWS WHAT TO SAY.
YOU'RE AN ASS.

14:02.080 --> 14:04.048
THAT'S THE FACT.
- I HAVE GOT TO FIX THIS.

14:04.080 --> 14:05.559
- IT'S THE WORST THING.
- IT'S NOT--

14:05.600 --> 14:06.874
- I MEAN,
IT'S THE WORST THING.

14:06.910 --> 14:08.252
IT'S THE HARDEST THING
TO RECOVER FROM.

14:08.290 --> 14:09.518
I'M SORRY.
IT'S JUST TRUE.

14:09.570 --> 14:11.424
- I THINK YOU CAN FIX IT.
I DON'T KNOW HOW.

14:11.470 --> 14:13.426
- WELL, I HAVE TO FIX IT,
BECAUSE I LOVE JABBAR,

14:13.470 --> 14:15.358
AND I LOVE JASMINE,
SO WHAT ARE MY OPTIONS?

14:15.400 --> 14:16.560
- I THINK YOU CAN.

14:16.610 --> 14:18.498
I DON'T KNOW WHAT THEY ARE,
BUT I THINK IT'S POSSIBLE.

14:18.540 --> 14:20.531
- HEY.

14:23.030 --> 14:26.136
- YOU DIDN'T SAY
HE WAS GONNA BE HERE.

14:26.170 --> 14:28.547
- HEY, ADAM!
ADAM!

14:28.590 --> 14:29.375
WILL YOU--HEY!

14:29.420 --> 14:32.207
WILL YOU PLEASE
LET ME APOLOGIZE?

14:32.250 --> 14:34.935
I WAS AN IDIOT, OKAY?
I WAS SELFISH.

14:34.970 --> 14:36.551
ARE YOU REALLY GONNA ACT

14:36.590 --> 14:38.034
LIKE YOU CAN'T HEAR ME
SAYING "SORRY"?

14:38.080 --> 14:40.287
- CROSBY, I DON'T CARE
THAT YOU'RE SORRY.

14:40.320 --> 14:42.117
I JUST DON'T CARE,
ALL RIGHT?

14:42.150 --> 14:44.186
I'M BUSY TRYING TO LOOK
AFTER MY SON,

14:44.220 --> 14:46.188
TRYING TO LOOK
AFTER MY FAMILY.

14:46.230 --> 14:48.562
YOU'RE NOT EVEN
ON MY RADAR.

14:50.060 --> 14:53.678
[car door closes,
engine turning]

15:01.310 --> 15:03.039
- THERE YOU GO.
THIRD ROUND.

15:03.070 --> 15:04.446
TELL 'EM TO ENJOY LUNCH.

15:04.480 --> 15:06.482
- YOU KNOW MY MOTTO--
SHOTS PAY THE RENT, BABY.

15:06.520 --> 15:07.999
- HEY, LOU,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

15:08.040 --> 15:09.314
I THOUGHT YOU HAD TO SLEEP
ALL DAY LIKE A BAT.

15:09.350 --> 15:10.658
- UH, DANNY QUIT.

15:10.700 --> 15:12.349
- OH, I WORKED
WITH HIM SATURDAY NIGHT.

15:12.390 --> 15:14.381
- QUIT ON SUNDAY.
- WHY?

15:14.430 --> 15:16.079
- ON TO NEW YORK.
HE'S GOT A DREAM.

15:16.120 --> 15:17.974
I DON'T KNOW.
- WELL, SO NOW WHAT HAPPENS?

15:18.020 --> 15:19.499
YOU JUST TAKE ALL THE SHIFTS?

15:19.530 --> 15:21.282
- WELL, UNTIL SHANAHAN FINDS
ANOTHER MANAGER.

15:21.330 --> 15:22.467
AND HE BETTER DO IT SOON,

15:22.500 --> 15:25.196
BECAUSE THESE DOUBLES
ARE KILLING ME.

15:25.230 --> 15:26.982
- HEY.

15:27.020 --> 15:29.227
WHAT ABOUT ME?

15:29.270 --> 15:30.544
- WELL, WHAT ABOUT YOU?

15:30.580 --> 15:33.196
- YOU KNOW,
TO BE THE NEW MANAGER.

15:33.240 --> 15:34.958
- YOU HAVEN'T BEEN HERE
THAT LONG.

15:35.000 --> 15:37.651
- I'VE BEEN HERE OVER A YEAR,
YOU KNOW, OFF AND ON.

15:37.690 --> 15:39.999
- I NEED SOME CONSISTENCY.
- NO, I COULD BE CONSISTENT.

15:40.040 --> 15:44.204
- WHAT, ARE YOU JONESING
TO MANAGE A BAR?

15:44.250 --> 15:46.764
- I'M, YOU KNOW, THINKING
ABOUT MY FUTURE.

15:46.800 --> 15:47.721
- HERE?

15:47.770 --> 15:49.658
- I DON'T KNOW, LOU.

15:49.700 --> 15:52.385
I MEAN, I DREAMED OF BEING
AN ARTIST OR A WRITER

15:52.430 --> 15:54.352
OR SOMETHING,
BUT I MEAN, COME ON.

15:54.400 --> 15:56.288
I GOT TO PAY THE RENT,
YOU KNOW?

15:56.330 --> 15:58.059
WHAT DO YOU GOT,
A LINE OF PEOPLE OUTSIDE?

15:58.090 --> 15:59.500
JUST PUT IN A GO|\OOD WORD FOR ME.

15:59.540 --> 16:01.121
OKAY, I'LL TELL HIM
YOU'RE INTERESTED, ALL RIGHT?

16:01.160 --> 16:02.388
- THANK YOU.

16:02.440 --> 16:03.782
- HIT ME.
DON'T LEAVE ME HANGING.

16:03.820 --> 16:05.230
LOVE YOU.

16:05.270 --> 16:09.024
I'LL BE IN THE OFFICE.
SELL SOME MORE SHOTS.

16:11.280 --> 16:12.759
[telephone rings]

16:12.790 --> 16:13.859
- YEAH?

16:13.900 --> 16:16.721
- I HAVE A JASMINE TRUSSELL
ON THE LINE FOR YOU.

16:16.760 --> 16:18.204
SHOULD I TAKE A MESSAGE?

16:18.250 --> 16:21.549
- NO, UH, PUT HER THROUGH.
THANKS.

16:21.600 --> 16:23.318
- HEY, JULIA.
IT'S JASMINE.

16:23.360 --> 16:24.804
- HI, JASMINE.

16:24.840 --> 16:26.660
- I...

16:26.700 --> 16:29.806
I JUST WANTED TO CALL
AND FIND OUT IF WE'RE STILL ON

16:29.850 --> 16:31.226
FOR THE SLEEPOVER TOMORROW.

16:31.260 --> 16:33.706
- YEAH, I-I WAS ACTUALLY GONNA
CALL YOU TOO.

16:33.750 --> 16:35.320
SO...

16:35.370 --> 16:36.462
ARE WE STILL ON?

16:36.510 --> 16:39.479
- YEAH.
I-I HOPE SO.

16:39.510 --> 16:43.025
JABBAR IS PRETTY AMPED UP
ABOUT IT.

16:43.070 --> 16:44.162
- YEAH, SO IS SYDNEY.

16:44.210 --> 16:47.065
I JUST--YOU KNOW?

16:47.100 --> 16:48.749
AS LONG AS YOU'RE OKAY
WITH IT.

16:48.800 --> 16:51.792
- OH, IT'S OKAY.

16:51.830 --> 16:54.242
AND--AND I'M OKAY.

16:54.280 --> 16:56.145
EVERYTHING'S OKAY.

16:56.180 --> 16:58.319
AND, UM...

16:58.360 --> 17:01.352
WE'D REALLY LOVE
FOR SYDNEY TO COME, SO...

17:01.390 --> 17:03.426
- WELL, WE WOULD LOVE
THAT TOO.

17:03.470 --> 17:04.732
- GOOD.

17:04.780 --> 17:06.771
- IS 4:00 TOO EARLY?

17:06.810 --> 17:08.607
- 4:00 IS GREAT.

17:08.640 --> 17:10.392
- ALL RIGHT, SEE YOU THEN.

17:10.440 --> 17:12.328
- OKAY, BYE.

17:12.370 --> 17:17.194
- WHILE THE OTHERS
START TO DISAGREE

17:20.100 --> 17:22.136
GONNA TURN IT AROUND

17:22.170 --> 17:26.823
FOR MOVING GROUNDS

