- HI.
- MOM, DAD, HI.

17:47.680 --> 17:49.671
COME ON IN.
- HOW ARE YOU?

17:49.720 --> 17:50.744
- GOOD.
HOW ARE YOU?

17:50.790 --> 17:51.882
- I'M GOOD.
- HEY.

17:51.930 --> 17:53.136
- HEY.
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

17:53.170 --> 17:54.273
- YEAH.

17:54.310 --> 17:57.165
WELL, YOU KNOW, YOUR SISTER
TOLD US WHAT HAPPENED.

17:57.210 --> 17:59.861
- WHAT EXACTLY
DID SHE TELL YOU?

17:59.900 --> 18:02.141
- WITH CROSBY AND THE STUFF,
YOU KNOW?

18:02.180 --> 18:03.340
- YEAH,
PRETTY MUCH EVERYTHING.

18:03.390 --> 18:04.618
- OKAY.

18:04.660 --> 18:05.831
- WHY DON'T YOU GUYS COME ON IN
AND SIT DOWN?

18:05.870 --> 18:08.737
- UM, HOW--HOW ARE YOU DOING?

18:08.770 --> 18:12.399
- WE'RE, UH, YOU KNOW--
WE'RE ALL DOING OKAY.

18:12.430 --> 18:14.534
- WE'RE GOOD.
- YEAH.

18:14.570 --> 18:17.391
- SO HOW'S--
HOW'S MY GRANDSON DOING?

18:17.440 --> 18:19.704
- TOUGH TO SAY.

18:19.750 --> 18:21.809
HE'S WORKING THROUGH THINGS
IN HIS OWN WAY,

18:21.850 --> 18:23.238
AT HIS OWN PACE.

18:23.270 --> 18:25.545
- SO MAYBE IT WAS
FOR THE BEST, THEN.

18:25.580 --> 18:27.161
- WELL, I DON'T KNOW

18:27.200 --> 18:28.758
THAT I'D EXACTLY PUT IT
THAT WAY, BUT--

18:28.790 --> 18:29.859
- HE WAS GONNA FIND OUT
ABOUT IT,

18:29.900 --> 18:31.686
SO SOONER'S
BETTER THAN LATER.

18:31.730 --> 18:33.869
- YOU KNOW, DAD,
I GOT TO SAY,

18:33.900 --> 18:35.413
I'M HAVING A TOUGH TIME
SITTING HERE LISTENING TO YOU

18:35.450 --> 18:36.769
TRY TO PUT A POSITIVE SPIN
ON THIS.

18:36.800 --> 18:38.904
YOU KNOW, GABY
HAS BEEN WORKING FOR US

18:38.940 --> 18:40.828
FOR OVER A YEAR TRYING
TO GAIN MAX'S TRUST,

18:40.870 --> 18:42.758
AND SHE QUIT
BECAUSE OF CROSBY.

18:42.810 --> 18:43.663
SO WE'RE NOT LOOKING
AT THIS

18:43.700 --> 18:45.588
LIKE SOME SORT
OF AWESOME DEVELOPMENT.

18:45.640 --> 18:47.801
- DO YOU GUYS WANT
ANY COFFEE OR ANYTHING?

18:47.850 --> 18:49.806
- NO, THANK YOU.
HAVE YOU TALKED TO YOUR BROTHER?

18:49.850 --> 18:50.919
- NO.

18:50.950 --> 18:52.838
- I DON'T THINK
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

18:52.890 --> 18:55.290
- YOU SHOULD TALK TO HIM,
DON'T YOU THINK?

18:55.340 --> 18:57.296
BLOOD IS THICKER THAN WATER.
COME ON.

18:57.340 --> 18:59.808
- I MEAN,
HE--HE MADE A MISTAKE.

18:59.860 --> 19:02.203
IT WAS A REALLY BAD THING
HE DID,

19:02.240 --> 19:04.652
BUT HE NEEDS TO TALK TO YOU.

19:04.690 --> 19:06.373
YOU'RE HIS BROTHER.

19:06.420 --> 19:09.480
- IS THIS WHY
YOU CAME OVER HERE?

19:09.520 --> 19:11.408
YOU CAME OVER HERE TO GET ME
TO--TO TALK TO CROSBY?

19:11.460 --> 19:12.484
IS THAT WHAT THIS IS?

19:12.530 --> 19:13.792
DO YOU KNOW
WHY HE'S IRRESPONSIBLE?

19:13.840 --> 19:15.284
IT'S BECAUSE OF YOU.
BOTH OF YOU ARE TO BLAME

19:15.320 --> 19:16.696
FOR LETTING HIM
GET AWAY WITH EVERYTHING,

19:16.740 --> 19:18.310
FOR LETTING HIM
OFF THE HOOK FOR EVERYTHING.

19:18.360 --> 19:19.759
YEAR AFTER YEAR,
YOU MAKE EXCUSES FOR HIM.

19:19.810 --> 19:21.459
YOU DO HIS LAUNDRY.
YOU LEND HIM MONEY.

19:21.500 --> 19:23.639
YOU--YOU BAIL HIM OUT.
HE'S A GROWN MAN!

19:23.670 --> 19:25.183
IT'S NOT MY RESPONSIBILITY
TO MAKE HIM

19:25.230 --> 19:26.538
FEEL BETTER ABOUT THIS!

19:26.570 --> 19:27.810
YOU KNOW, I'M SPENDING
ALL MY ENERGY

19:27.850 --> 19:28.987
TRYING TO CLEAN UP THIS MESS
THAT CROSBY MADE.

19:29.020 --> 19:31.716
HE CHEATED ON HIS FIANCEE.
IT DIRECTLY AFFECTED MAX.

19:31.750 --> 19:34.401
AND I DON'T CARE IF HE
DIDN'T MEAN TO HURT ANYBODY.

19:34.440 --> 19:35.850
HE DID,
JUST LIKE HE ALWAYS DOES!

19:35.890 --> 19:36.857
HE'S SELFISH.

19:36.890 --> 19:38.300
AND FOR YOU, OF ALL PEOPLE,

19:38.340 --> 19:41.343
TO SYMPATHIZE WITH THAT
IS UNBELIEVABLE TO ME.

19:41.380 --> 19:43.826
- HONEY?

19:43.870 --> 19:45.792
HONEY?

19:51.010 --> 19:53.570
- FIVE, SIX, SEVEN, EIGHT.

19:53.600 --> 19:56.398
AND ONE, TWO, THREE,
