FIVE, SIX, SEVEN, EIGHT.

20:03.400 --> 20:04.776
AND ONE, TWO, THREE,
AND FOUR--

20:04.820 --> 20:06.640
- HEY.
HEY.

20:06.680 --> 20:08.329
CAN I HAVE, LIKE,
A SECOND OF YOUR TIME?

20:08.370 --> 20:09.928
- I'M IN THE MIDDLE
OF CLASS RIGHT NOW.

20:09.960 --> 20:13.828
- OKAY, WELL,
IT'S IMPORTANT.

20:13.860 --> 20:17.273
YOU--YOU HAVE TO TALK TO ME.

20:17.310 --> 20:18.447
LISTEN...

20:18.490 --> 20:20.720
- DON'T YOU DARE TELL ME
WHAT I HAVE TO DO.

20:20.770 --> 20:21.998
- I JUST WANT, FOR ONE SECOND--
- NO, NO.

20:22.040 --> 20:23.905
I DON'T WANT TO HEAR IT.

20:23.940 --> 20:25.805
YOU KNOW I'M BARELY HOLDING ON
RIGHT NOW?

20:25.840 --> 20:27.831
DO YOU UNDERSTAND THAT?
DO YOU?

20:27.880 --> 20:29.871
WHAT YOU DID TO ME
MAKES ME SICK.

20:29.910 --> 20:31.707
WHAT YOU DID TO OUR FAMILY
MAKES ME SICK.

20:31.740 --> 20:32.980
I DON'T EVEN WANT
TO LOOK AT YOU.

20:33.020 --> 20:34.294
DON'T COME HERE AGAIN.

20:34.330 --> 20:36.673
DON'T COME HERE AGAIN.

20:36.710 --> 20:39.986
- [sighs]

20:40.030 --> 20:42.021
[door closes]

20:42.060 --> 20:43.857
- OKAY, MAX, LET'S BOOGIE.

20:43.890 --> 20:45.027
WE'RE LATE.

20:45.070 --> 20:46.583
- WHY ISN'T MOM TAKING ME
TO SCHOOL?

20:46.620 --> 20:49.339
- BECAUSE SHE HAS TO RUN
AN ERRAND WITH HADDIE.

20:49.380 --> 20:50.927
- THESE ARE THE WRONG SHOES.

20:50.970 --> 20:52.062
- MAX,
WE DON'T HAVE TIME, OKAY?

20:52.110 --> 20:53.657
- I WANT TO WEAR MY BLUE SHOES.
- JUST PUT THOSE ON.

