21:10.850 --> 21:13.739
[sighs]

21:20.900 --> 21:21.969
MAX, WHAT IF I TOLD YOU

21:22.000 --> 21:23.581
YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO GO
TO SCHOOL TODAY?

21:23.620 --> 21:24.928
- BUT I DO.
IT'S THURSDAY.

21:24.970 --> 21:26.062
- YOU DON'T.

21:26.110 --> 21:27.725
YOU DON'T HAVE TO GO
TO SCHOOL TODAY.

21:27.760 --> 21:29.580
- YES, I DO.
IT'S THURSDAY.

21:29.630 --> 21:30.790
- WHAT IF,
INSTEAD OF GOING TO SCHOOL,

21:30.840 --> 21:32.728
YOU AND I GO
TO GALAXY POINT PARK

21:32.770 --> 21:34.078
AND RIDE ROLLER COASTERS
ALL DAY LONG?

21:34.120 --> 21:36.315
JUST YOU AND ME.
HOW'S THAT FOR A SURPRISE?

21:36.360 --> 21:38.396
COME ON.
- I DON'T LIKE SURPRISES.

21:38.430 --> 21:40.421
- OKAY.

21:41.990 --> 21:43.912
REMEMBER THE VELOCERATOR--

21:43.950 --> 21:46.703
SCARIEST, FASTEST RIDE
IN ALL OF NORTHERN CALIFORNIA?

21:46.750 --> 21:48.126
- YEAH, I KNOW.
IT SAYS SO ON THE POSTER.

21:48.160 --> 21:49.127
- THAT WAS YOUR FAVORITE.

21:49.160 --> 21:50.809
YOU WANTED TO RIDE THAT,
LIKE, A DOZEN TIMES.

21:50.860 --> 21:52.088
- IT'S THE ONE
ON THE MOBIUS TRACK, RIGHT?

21:52.130 --> 21:53.097
- THAT'S RIGHT.

21:53.130 --> 21:54.927
- THE ONE THAT GOES
FORWARDS AND BACIONARDS?

21:54.960 --> 21:55.756
- THAT'S RIGHT.

21:55.790 --> 21:56.996
- CAN WE GO ON IT
MORE THAN ONCE?

21:57.030 --> 21:59.339
- WE CAN GO ON THE VELOCERATOR
AS MANY TIMES AS YOU WANT.

21:59.380 --> 22:00.517
WE'LL ONLY BREAK
FOR MEALS, OKAY?

22:00.560 --> 22:02.346
WE WILL GO ON THE VELOCERATOR
TILL THE PARK CLOSES.

22:02.390 --> 22:04.529
YOU MAY NEVER WANT TO GO
ON THE VELOCERATOR AGAIN.

22:04.560 --> 22:07.620
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

22:07.670 --> 22:08.830
- OKAY.

22:08.870 --> 22:09.837
- YES!
- YES!

22:09.880 --> 22:10.949
- ALL RIGHT!
- AWESOME!

22:15.500 --> 22:17.536
- SO LOUIS TELLS ME
YOU ARE INTERESTED IN MANAGING.

22:17.570 --> 22:18.980
- DEFINITELY.
- WHY?

22:19.020 --> 22:21.500
- WHY?
HAVE YOU NEVER SEEN CHEERS?

22:21.540 --> 22:22.677
OKAY?
[chuckles]

22:22.720 --> 22:25.473
WHAT LOOKS BETTER THAN,
UH, YOU KNOW, TED DANSON'S JOB?

22:25.510 --> 22:26.716
- WELL,
TED DANSON WAS THE OWNER.

22:26.750 --> 22:28.399
- RIGHT.

22:28.450 --> 22:29.712
THAT'S UP NEXT.

22:29.760 --> 22:31.648
NO, SERIOUSLY, I, UM--

22:31.690 --> 22:34.443
YOU KNOW, I'VE JUST SPENT A LOT
OF TIME BEING A BARTENDER,

22:34.490 --> 22:35.821
AND, UH, I THINK
I'D BE GOOD AT IT.

22:35.870 --> 22:37.098
I'M LOOKING TO EXPAND.

22:37.140 --> 22:38.243
- OKAY, BUT YOU DO KNOW

22:38.280 --> 22:40.840
THAT IT PAYS ABOUT 30%
LESS THAN BARTENDING, RIGHT?

22:40.870 --> 22:42.553
- NO.
- YEAH.

22:42.600 --> 22:44.522
YEAH, MANAGERS,
THEY DON'T TAKE HOME TIPS.

22:44.570 --> 22:46.379
SO YOU ACTUALLY GET A SALARY.

22:46.430 --> 22:48.398
AND I CAN GUARANTEE
YOUR CURRENT TAKE-HOME PAY

22:48.430 --> 22:49.874
IS GONNA GET HIT PRETTY HARD.

22:49.920 --> 22:51.876
- UM, HUH.

22:51.920 --> 22:54.127
- CAN I MAKE AN OBSERVATION?
- YEAH.

22:54.160 --> 22:55.980
- THE CUSTOMERS--
THEY ALL LOVE YOU, OKAY?

22:56.020 --> 22:57.669
AND AS FAR AS I'M CONCERNED,

22:57.720 --> 22:59.779
YOU CAN WORK AS MANY SHIFTS
AS YOU WANT, OKAY?

22:59.820 --> 23:02.129
YES, MAYBE SOMETIMES YOU'RE
A LITTLE ERRATIC, WHATEVER.

23:02.170 --> 23:05.549
YOU DON'T BRING ME DRAMA,
AND I LOVE THAT.

23:05.590 --> 23:08.514
BUT I DON'T THINK
YOU SHOULD BE A MANAGER.

23:08.550 --> 23:10.108
YOU KNOW, AND I'D HATE
TO SEE YOU GET BURNT OUT

23:10.140 --> 23:11.823
AFTER SIX MONTHS
'CAUSE, YOU KNOW,

23:11.870 --> 23:14.623
YOU HATE SCHEDULING
EVERYBODY'S SHIFTS.

23:14.660 --> 23:16.969
- YEAH.
- YEAH.

23:17.010 --> 23:19.046
- WELL, THANKS, PETE.

23:19.080 --> 23:21.048
- COME TO ME ANYTIME.

23:23.500 --> 23:26.185
- IT'S THIS WAY, DAD.
- ARE YOU SURE?

23:26.230 --> 23:28.084
- YES. NO, BUT FIRST
WE HAVE TO RIDE--

23:28.130 --> 23:31.816
NO. DAD! FIRST WE HAVE TO
RIDE THE FURY...

23:31.850 --> 23:33.852
[cell phone rings]

23:33.890 --> 23:35.050
- EXCUSE ME.
WHAT ARE YOU SELLING HERE?

23:35.100 --> 23:36.783
- HEY, HONEY.
- HEY, HONEY. HI.

23:36.820 --> 23:39.448
CAN YOU HEAR ME?
- YEAH. I'M RIGHT HERE.

23:39.480 --> 23:40.924
- WHERE ARE YOU?
I CAN BARELY HEAR YOU.

23:40.970 --> 23:42.995
- I AM AT GALAXY POINT PARK.

23:43.040 --> 23:44.621
- YOU'RE WHAT?

23:44.660 --> 23:45.752
- MAX AND I
ARE PLAYING HOOKY TODAY,

23:45.800 --> 23:46.960
SO WE CAME OUT
TO GALAXY POINT.

23:47.010 --> 23:48.864
WE'RE GONNA RIDE
THE VELOCERATOR.

23:48.910 --> 23:50.719
HEY, MAX, STAY CLOSE TO ME.
WHAT?

23:50.770 --> 23:52.692
- OKAY, ADAM, I DON'T THINK
THAT THAT'S SUCH A GOOD IDEA.

23:52.740 --> 23:55.732
- I KNOW, HONEY, BUT WE'RE
HAVING A FANTASTIC TIME, OKAY?

23:55.770 --> 23:56.839
MAX.
- I NEED $6.

23:56.880 --> 23:58.973
- I SAY THIS OUT OF LOVE,
BUT YOU'VE GONE ROGUE.

23:59.020 --> 24:00.567
ADAM.
- YEAH?

24:00.610 --> 24:02.054
HONEY, LISTEN,
IT'S JUST ONE DAY, OKAY?

24:02.090 --> 24:03.193
IT'S NOT A BIG DEAL.

24:03.230 --> 24:05.460
- IT IS A BIG DEAL.
WE HAVE TO STICK WITH THE PLAN.

24:05.510 --> 24:07.535
DR. PELICAN SAID
TO STICK WITH HIS ROUTINE,

24:07.580 --> 24:08.501
AND THIS IS NOT HIS ROUTINE.

24:08.550 --> 24:10.051
- KRISTINA, YOU AND I
HAVE BEEN PARENTS

24:10.100 --> 24:11.818
FOR THE EXACT SAME
AMOUNT OF TIME, OKAY?

24:11.860 --> 24:13.236
EVERYTHING IS GONNA BE
JUST FINE.

24:13.270 --> 24:15.830
IT'S UNDER CONTROL.
DON'T WORRY, ALL RIGHT?

24:15.860 --> 24:16.827
I LOVE YOU.
BYE.

24:16.860 --> 24:19.442
- HELLO?
- ALL RIGHT!

24:28.600 --> 24:30.704
- THAT IS SO COOL!

24:30.740 --> 24:32.708
HEY, DID YOU KNOW
THAT THE SIDEWINDER...

24:32.740 --> 24:34.879
IS AN INVERTED ELEMENT
ON A ROLLER COASTER

24:34.920 --> 24:37.502
WHERE IT MAKES A 90-DEGREE TURN
WHILE THE TRAIN IS INVERTED?

24:37.540 --> 24:38.746
- I DID NOT KNOW THAT.

24:38.780 --> 24:40.748
- AND THE FASTEST COASTER
IN THE WORLD IS IN ABU DHABI.

24:40.780 --> 24:43.783
IT GOES FROM ZERO
TO 150 MILES AN HOUR

24:43.820 --> 24:44.889
IN FOUR SECONDS.

24:44.930 --> 24:46.192
- WOW.
THAT IS FAST.

24:46.240 --> 24:47.639
- IF YOU SIT IN THE FRONT,

24:47.690 --> 24:49.658
YOU HAVE TO WEAR
PROTECTIVE GOGGLES.

24:49.690 --> 24:50.896
IT'S GONNA BE AWESOME!

24:50.930 --> 24:52.101
WHOO!

24:52.140 --> 24:54.062
I JUST CAN'T WAIT.
I CAN'T WAIT.

24:54.110 --> 24:55.793
I CAN'T WAIT,
I CAN'T WAIT, I CAN'T WAIT.

24:56.870 --> 24:58.838
- HEY.
- HI!

24:58.870 --> 25:00.838
- HEY.
- HEY, HONEY.

25:00.870 --> 25:02.690
HEY, JABBAR, SYDNEY'S HERE.

25:02.740 --> 25:03.525
- HI, SYDNEY.

25:03.570 --> 25:05.526
- HI. I GOT
A NEW PRETTY ERASER.

25:05.570 --> 25:06.707
- OH, YOU GUYS LOOK GREAT.

25:06.740 --> 25:08.082
- AW, THANKS.
- THANK YOU.

25:08.120 --> 25:09.701
- IS THERE A SPECIAL OCCASION?

25:09.740 --> 25:11.742
- UH, IT IS OFFICIALLY
OUR EIGHTH--

25:11.780 --> 25:14.010
- EIGHTH DAY EATING NO SUGAR.

25:14.060 --> 25:16.290
- WOW.
- YEAH.

25:16.340 --> 25:17.648
SO WE'RE CELEBRATING.

25:17.680 --> 25:19.307
WE'RE GOING
TO A RAW-FOOD RESTAURANT.

25:19.340 --> 25:20.716
- MMM. YES.

25:20.760 --> 25:21.886
- THAT'S--THAT'S REALLY HARD.

25:21.930 --> 25:23.579
- YES.
- GOOD FOR YOU GUYS.

25:23.620 --> 25:25.588
- I THINK IT'S THE FIRST DATE
WE'VE HAD ON A WEEKDAY

25:25.620 --> 25:26.723
SINCE, UH,
BEFORE SYDNEY WAS BORN.

25:26.760 --> 25:27.897
- NO, THAT'S AN EXAGGERATION.

25:27.940 --> 25:29.555
- NO, I DON'T THINK
I AM EXAGGERATING.

25:29.590 --> 25:31.729
- YEAH, YOU ARE, BABE.
- WELL, REGARDLESS, THANK YOU.

25:31.770 --> 25:33.795
THIS--THIS IS FANTASTIC.
- YOU'RE WELCOME.

25:33.840 --> 25:35.102
- OKAY.

25:35.150 --> 25:37.596
- ALL RIGHT, WELL, I'LL PICK HER
UP FIRST THING IN THE MORNING?

25:37.630 --> 25:40.804
- YOU KNOW, ANYTIME.
I'M NOT WORKING TOMORROW, SO...

25:40.840 --> 25:44.298
HAVE FUN.
[laughs tearfully]

25:44.330 --> 25:45.672
- JASMINE.

25:45.710 --> 25:47.849
- I'M FINE.
I'M FINE. I'M FINE.

25:47.890 --> 25:49.983
I'M FINE.

25:53.060 --> 25:55.824
HEY, GUYS, WHO WANTS
TO PLAY HIDE-AND-SEEK

25:55.860 --> 25:57.304
ISRAELI ARMY STYLE?
- COME HERE. COME HERE.

25:57.340 --> 25:58.898
- I DO.
- YES?

25:58.930 --> 25:59.965
ALL RIGHT, HERE IT IS...

26:00.000 --> 26:01.820
- I'M SORRY.
- NO, DON'T BE SORRY.

26:01.870 --> 26:03.098
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
- YOU GUYS SHOULD GO.

26:03.140 --> 26:04.004
I'M FINE.
I'LL BE OKAY.

26:04.040 --> 26:06.144
- HEY, WE ARE HERE NOW.
DON'T BE SILLY.

26:06.180 --> 26:07.761
WE CAN--WE CAN HANG OUT.

26:07.800 --> 26:09.210
- NO, BUT YOU LOOK SO PRETTY.

26:09.250 --> 26:11.935
AND H THOUGHT THIS WAS
A SPECIAL OCCASION FOR YOU TWO.

26:11.980 --> 26:13.186
- NO, WE WE'RE JUST
GONNA GO EAT.

26:13.220 --> 26:14.664
- REALLY?
- DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

26:14.710 --> 26:15.972
WE CAN GO EAT ANYTIME.

26:16.020 --> 26:18.011
- OKAY, UH, WHO HERE
WANTS SOME PIZZA?

26:18.050 --> 26:20.086
WHAT DO YOU GUYS LIKE ON IT--
BRUSSELS SPROUTS?

26:20.130 --> 26:21.631
- THANKS.
- OF COURSE.

26:21.680 --> 26:24.843
- YOU DON'T LIKE
BRUSSELS SPROUTS? THAT'S WEIRD.

26:27.930 --> 26:29.090
- I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.

26:29.130 --> 26:31.712
WE'RE ACTUALLY
ON THE VELOCERATOR.

26:31.760 --> 26:33.648
WE'RE ON IT.
- ALL RIGHT.

26:33.690 --> 26:35.305
THIS IS GONNA BE GREAT.
- YES, YES IT IS.

26:35.350 --> 26:36.829
IT'S GONNA BE REALLY COOL.

26:36.870 --> 26:38.314
- ALL RIGHT,
LET'S MAKE SURE WE KEEP

26:38.350 --> 26:40.079
OUR HANDS AND ARMS
INSIDE AT ALL TIMES.

26:40.110 --> 26:41.839
YOU READY?

26:41.870 --> 26:43.007
- WHY ISN'T IT GOING?

26:43.040 --> 26:44.735
- WELL, THERE'S A FEW
MORE PEOPLE HAVE TO GET ON...

26:44.770 --> 26:47.352
- NO, IT SHOULD BE GOING
BY NOW.

26:47.390 --> 26:48.903
- I DON'T KNOW.

26:48.950 --> 26:52.158
- WE'RE SORRY, BUT
THE VELOCERATOR NEEDS REPAIRS

26:52.190 --> 26:56.229
AND WILL BE CLOSED
FOR THE REST OF THE DAY.

26:56.260 --> 26:57.887
- WHAT?

26:57.920 --> 27:00.980
- OKAY, LISTEN, MAX, THIS
IS SOMETHING WE DIDN'T PLAN ON,

27:01.030 --> 27:02.782
BUT WE HAVE TO GET OFF
THE RIDE NOW.

27:02.820 --> 27:04.993
- NO, WE DON'T. YOU SAID
WE WOULD RIDE THE VELOCERATOR

27:05.030 --> 27:06.406
AS MANY TIMES AS I WANTED.

27:06.450 --> 27:07.894
- I KNOW I DID,
BUT THEY HAVE TO MAKE REPAIRS.

27:07.930 --> 27:09.067
- NO, YOU TOOK ME
OUT OF SCHOOL

27:09.110 --> 27:11.442
SO THAT WE COULD COME HERE
AND RIDE THE VELOCERATOR.

27:11.490 --> 27:14.653
WE CHANGED
EVERYTHING ABOUT THE DAY

27:14.700 --> 27:15.860
TO COME HERE AND RIDE THIS.

27:15.910 --> 27:17.309
NO, WE HAVE TO RIDE IT!

27:17.350 --> 27:19.386
- THERE'S ANOTHER RIDE
RIGHT OVER THERE.

27:19.430 --> 27:21.830
- NO, I DON'T WANT
ANOTHER RIDE!

27:21.880 --> 27:23.734
I WANT TO RIDE
THE VELOCERATOR!

27:23.780 --> 27:26.419
IT'S NOT FAIR! IT'S NOT FAIR!
- MAX, HEY, HEY, HEY.

27:26.470 --> 27:28.085
- IT'S NOT FAIR!

27:28.120 --> 27:29.985
- MAX! EXCUSE ME.
MAX!

27:30.020 --> 27:31.772
- IT'S NOT FAIR!
- MAX!

27:31.820 --> 27:32.775
-AAH!

27:32.820 --> 27:34.788
- MAX, HEY.
EXCUSE ME.

27:34.820 --> 27:35.787
MAX.
MAX, HEY, HEY, HEY.

27:35.820 --> 27:37.162
- IT'S NOT FAIR!
YOU PROMISED!

27:37.200 --> 27:39.953
- MAX, IT'S OKAY, ALL RIGHT?
- YOU PROMISED...

27:40.000 --> 27:43.299
WE WOULD GO ON THE VELOCERATOR
AS MANY TIMES AS I WANTED!

27:43.350 --> 27:46.376
- IT BROKE DOWN.
I CAN'T--HEY, MAX!

27:46.420 --> 27:48.240
- YOU SAID!

27:48.280 --> 27:50.840
AAH!

27:53.180 --> 27:56.695
- YOU'RE OKAY.
YOU'RE OKAY.

28:03.160 --> 28:06.323
[rock music playing]
- HEY, HEY, HEY.

28:06.370 --> 28:07.189
HEY.

28:07.230 --> 28:09.289
- UH, WHAT ARE YOU DOING
ON MY BOAT?

28:09.340 --> 28:10.819
- COME ON, SIR, COULD YOU JUST
LOWER THE MUSIC

28:10.860 --> 28:11.929
A LITTLE BIT, PLEASE, HUH?

28:11.960 --> 28:13.234
IT'S BEEN GOING ALL NIGHT.

28:13.270 --> 28:15.204
- I DON'T THINK
I INVITED YOU ON MY BOAT.

28:15.240 --> 28:16.275
- HEY, OTHER PEOPLE LIVE HERE.

28:16.310 --> 28:18.369
HOW ABOUT JUST A LITTLE BIT
OF CONSIDERATION?

28:18.420 --> 28:20.376
NO, NO, THERE ARE OTHER PEOPLE
IN THIS WORLD, YEAH.

28:20.420 --> 28:22.035
- WHY DON'T YOU TURN
YOUR ASS AROUND

28:22.070 --> 28:22.934
AND GO BACK TO YOUR BOAT?

28:22.970 --> 28:24.722
- YOU DON'T NEED
TO TALK TO ME LIKE THAT.

28:24.770 --> 28:26.169
- I THINK YOU'RE ON MY BOAT,
SO I THINK I'LL TALK TO YOU

28:26.220 --> 28:28.973
HOW I WANT!
GET OFF MY BOAT!

28:31.290 --> 28:34.179
- COME ON, MOUTH.
COME ON.

28:39.090 --> 28:43.026
[indistinct
police radio chatter]

28:54.110 --> 28:56.249
- I PAID YOUR BAIL.

29:00.080 --> 29:01.798
- I MESSED UP.

29:01.840 --> 29:05.833
- YEAH, YOU DID.

29:05.880 --> 29:07.973
- I MEAN...

29:08.020 --> 29:09.567
I REALLY MESSED UP.

29:09.600 --> 29:12.569
[dramatic music]

29:23.340 --> 29:26.093
- HE'S ASLEEP.

29:26.140 --> 29:27.471
- THAT'S GOOD.

29:27.520 --> 29:30.967
THAT'S GOOD.

29:31.010 --> 29:33.035
[exhales deeply]
- I'M SORRY, KRISTINA.

29:33.080 --> 29:36.049
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I WAS THINKING.

29:38.010 --> 29:39.830
- YOU WERE THINKING

29:39.880 --> 29:41.142
YOU WANTED TO HAVE
A GOOD TIME WITH YOUR SON

29:41.190 --> 29:43.977
AND CONNECT WITH HIM,
AND YOU DID. YOU DID.

29:44.020 --> 29:45.499
- I WAS JUST TRYING
TO GET HIM OUT OF THE HOUSE,

29:45.540 --> 29:47.292
AND HE HAD TO HAVE
HIS PARTICULAR PAIR OF SHOES,

29:47.330 --> 29:49.298
AND I...

29:49.330 --> 29:53.334
I DIDN'T WANT HIM
TO FEEL LIMITED, YOU KNOW?

29:53.370 --> 29:55.304
AND I...

29:55.340 --> 29:57.137
[voice breaking] I JUST WANTED
TO FORGET ABOUT EVERYTHING

29:57.170 --> 29:58.398
FOR ONE DAMN DAY,
YOU KNOW?

29:58.450 --> 30:01.965
AND SHOW HIM THAT WE COULD GO
OUT AND HAVE A HAPPY MEMORY.

30:02.000 --> 30:04.036
- IT'S OKAY, HONEY.

30:04.070 --> 30:06.868
- YOU KNOW, I JUST DIDN'T WANT
HIM TO FEEL SO ALONE.

30:06.900 --> 30:08.959
- HE HAD FUN.

30:09.010 --> 30:13.356
- WHY AM I NOT STRONG?

30:13.390 --> 30:15.017
- HERE.

30:18.980 --> 30:20.083
- ANYWAY,
I THINK YOU'RE RIGHT.

30:20.120 --> 30:23.055
I THINK THAT WE SHOULD...

30:23.090 --> 30:26.332
TRY TO TALK TO HIM AGAIN
ABOUT HIS ASPERGER'S.

30:26.370 --> 30:29.089
- OKAY. I THINK
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

30:29.130 --> 30:32.099
- WE CAN USE
THE PELICAN SCRIPT...

30:34.210 --> 30:36.371
AS A GUIDE.
- [laughs]

30:36.420 --> 30:38.991
OKAY, AS A GUIDE.
- [sighs]

30:40.970 --> 30:43.416
YOU'RE A GREAT DAD.

30:43.460 --> 30:45.667
- I HAVE MY MOMENTS.

30:45.700 --> 30:49.045
- YOU'RE A GREAT DAD.

30:49.080 --> 30:50.900
- YEAH.

31:00.030 --> 31:00.883
- SARAH, HI.
- AAH!

31:00.920 --> 31:02.057
- OH, HI.
- OH, MY GOD! OH, MY GOD!

31:02.100 --> 31:04.500
- I'M SORRY. I WAS--I WAS ABOUT
TO KNOCK ON THE DOOR.

31:04.550 --> 31:05.403
I DIDN'T GET THERE.

31:05.440 --> 31:06.884
- THIS IS NOT THE DOOR
WHERE YOU KNOCK.

31:06.930 --> 31:08.545
THAT IS THE DOOR.

31:08.590 --> 31:10.239
- I DON'T KNOW WHICH DOOR
IS THE RIGHT DOOR.

31:10.280 --> 31:12.032
THIS COMING FROM THE CAT BURGLAR
OUTSIDE MY APARTMENT.

31:12.070 --> 31:14.550
- THE CAT BURGLAR WORKED DURING
THE DAY--THAT'S NOT SCARY.

31:14.590 --> 31:16.273
- YOU KNOW, I GET A LITTLE
FREAKED OUT IN THE DAYTIME.

31:16.320 --> 31:20.279
I CAME BY TO RETURN
YOUR READING MATERIAL.

31:20.320 --> 31:22.185
- OH.

31:22.220 --> 31:25.041
- I'M--I'M SORRY.
I SHOULD HAVE CALLED.

31:25.090 --> 31:27.149
IJUST, UM...

31:27.190 --> 31:29.010
I JUST THOUGHT I'D...
- NO.

31:29.050 --> 31:31.120
- I DON'T KNOW--
JUST COME BY.

31:31.160 --> 31:33.299
IT'S NOT REALLY ANY FUN TO TALK
ABOUT WRITING OVER THE PHONE.

31:33.330 --> 31:35.150
- RIGHT. THIS IS GONNA BE
A LOT OF FUN.

31:35.200 --> 31:37.293
I CAN TELL.
SO HAVE A SEAT.

31:37.340 --> 31:40.093
- THIS IS GOOD.
UM, SO...

31:40.130 --> 31:41.609
- SO LET ME JUST SAVE YOU.

31:41.650 --> 31:42.787
UH, IF I REMEMBER
HOW THIS GOES,

31:42.830 --> 31:45.446
IS YOU START OFF WITH TWO
OR THREE KIND OF GENERIC,

31:45.480 --> 31:47.243
POSITIVE COMMENTS
ABOUT MY WRITING,

31:47.280 --> 31:49.168
YOU KNOW, TO MAKE ME
FEEL GOOD ABOUT MYSELF.

31:49.210 --> 31:50.199
AND THEN YOU FOLLOW THOSE UP

31:50.250 --> 31:53.003
WITH TWO OR THREE
SUPER-SPECIFIC CRITICISMS

31:53.040 --> 31:54.382
WHICH ARE SO SOUL CRUSHING,

31:54.420 --> 31:57.309
BECAUSE I REALIZE IN THAT MOMENT
HOW TRUE THEY ARE,

31:57.360 --> 31:59.180
SO IF YOU WANT TO JUST SKIP
TO THOSE,

31:59.220 --> 32:00.664
THAT'S FINE, 'CAUSE I PROBABLY
WON'T REMEMBER

32:00.710 --> 32:02.496
THE POSITIVE COMMENTS
BY THAT TIME ANYWAY,

32:02.540 --> 32:05.941
PROVIDED THERE ARE ANY,
WHICH MAY BE TOO HOPEFUL.

32:05.990 --> 32:06.979
[sighs]
WHAT?

32:07.020 --> 32:09.500
- NOTHING.
YOU JUST, UH...

32:09.540 --> 32:12.236
YOU JUST REDUCED MY LIFE'S WORK
AS AN ENGLISH TEACHER,

32:12.270 --> 32:14.022
SO I'M FEELING
A-A LITTLE UNNERVED.

32:14.070 --> 32:15.503
- OH, GOD.
- I'LL GET OVER IT.

32:15.550 --> 32:17.404
- NO, NO, I'M SORRY.
I'M AN IDIOT. I'M SO SORRY.

32:17.450 --> 32:18.997
- NO, IT WAS IMPRESSIVE.
- I'M JUST A LITTLE NERVOUS.

32:19.040 --> 32:20.689
BUT I CAN TAKE IT,
SO I'M GLAD YOU CAME.

32:20.730 --> 32:22.755
THANK YOU. GO AHEAD,
WHATEVER YOU HAVE TO SAY.

32:22.800 --> 32:24.449
- OKAY. ARE YOU SURE?
YES.

32:24.490 --> 32:27.698
- OKAY.
SO, UH, WELL, FIRSTLY...

32:27.730 --> 32:30.005
- OH, I'M SORRY. I JUST DON'T
WANT TO BE IN THIS CHAIR,

32:30.050 --> 32:31.620
'CAUSE IT JUST IS NOT--
I JUST WANT TO SIT...

32:31.670 --> 32:33.012
- OKAY.

32:33.050 --> 32:34.210
- I JUST WANT TO BE
SO I CAN REALLY...

32:34.260 --> 32:35.978
- YEAH.
THIS IS A GOOD PLACE FOR YOU.

32:36.020 --> 32:40.229
UM, SO MY MAIN IMPRESSION
IS THAT IT'S NOT A STORY.

32:40.260 --> 32:41.579
- OKAY. I KNOW.
NO, NO, NO, LISTEN.

32:41.610 --> 32:43.089
- SARAH.
SARAH, SHUT UP.

32:43.130 --> 32:44.745
PLEASE, SHUT UP.
- NO, I CAN'T.

32:44.790 --> 32:46.337
IT JUST--
IT CAME OUT LIKE, "BLAH."

32:46.370 --> 32:48.019
- SARAH, PLEASE,
STOP, STOP, STOP.

32:48.060 --> 32:49.994
I DIDN'T SAY IT WAS BAD.
IT'S NOT--IT'S NOT A STORY.

32:50.030 --> 32:52.544
IT'S MORE OF A PLAY, OKAY?

32:52.590 --> 32:54.729
YOUR CHARACTERS ARE--
ARE FRESH.

32:54.760 --> 32:57.172
THEIR VOICES ARE--
ARE CRYSTAL CLEAR,

32:57.210 --> 33:00.031
AND ALL OF THE ACTION
IS TOLD THROUGH THE DIALOGUE,

33:00.080 --> 33:03.072
WHICH, INCIDENTALLY,
IS INCREDIBLY FUNNY.

33:03.110 --> 33:05.806
- IT IS?
- YEAH, IT IS.

33:05.840 --> 33:09.082
NOW, I-I-I DO HAVE
TWO CRITICISMS.

33:09.120 --> 33:12.009
SO THE FIRST ONE
IS YOUR HANDWRITING'S READABLE,

33:12.050 --> 33:13.324
BUT I THINK
FOR YOUR NEXT DRAFT,

33:13.370 --> 33:15.258
YOU SHOULD ACTUALLY TYPE
YOUR WORK.

33:15.300 --> 33:17.018
- TYPE IT. YEAH.
OKAY, AND?

33:17.060 --> 33:20.439
- AND, TWO,
YOU HAVE TO FINISH IT.

33:20.480 --> 33:23.813
YOU NEED ACT TWO.

33:23.860 --> 33:27.159
AND, UM...

33:27.210 --> 33:29.724
AND THAT'S IT.

33:31.690 --> 33:32.827
- THAT'S IT?

33:32.870 --> 33:35.691
- YEAH.

33:35.730 --> 33:39.314
IT'S REALLY, REALLY GOOD.

33:39.360 --> 33:41.567
SO...

33:43.150 --> 33:45.289
CONGRATULATIONS,
SARAH BRAVERMAN.

33:45.330 --> 33:48.299
YOU ARE A PLAYWRIGHT.

33:52.130 --> 33:54.166
WAS IT HARD TO DO?

33:54.200 --> 33:56.782
- UM, NO, I MEAN,
THAT'S THE THING.

33:56.820 --> 34:00.779
IT JUST KIND OF...

34:00.830 --> 34:03.344
NO.

34:03.380 --> 34:06.349
NO.
- WOW.

34:07.730 --> 34:11.211
- SO JUST--I'M SORRY.
JUST TO BE CLEAR.

34:13.490 --> 34:14.878
YOU LIKED IT?

34:14.910 --> 34:16.559
- YES.

34:16.600 --> 34:20.707
I REALLY DID.

34:20.740 --> 34:24.562
- THAT'S JUST...

34:24.610 --> 34:28.091
- IT'S BEAUTIFULLY WRITTEN.

34:31.550 --> 34:34.519
WELL, I GUESS I'LL, UH--

34:34.550 --> 34:37.678
I'LL SEE YOU AROUND, SARAH.

34:37.730 --> 34:40.619
- I'LL SEE YOU AROUND, MARK.

34:40.660 --> 34:43.106
- ALL RIGHT.

34:53.470 --> 34:56.325
- HEY.

35:03.170 --> 35:06.469
THANK YOU.

35:06.510 --> 35:08.819
- YOU'RE--YOU'RE WELCOME.

35:42.240 --> 35:44.640
- SO, BUDDY,
DO YOU REMEMBER LAST YEAR

35:44.690 --> 35:46.419
WHEN YOU WENT
TO OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY

35:46.450 --> 35:47.894
TO GET MORE COMFORTABLE
IN YOUR BODY?

35:47.930 --> 35:49.898
REMEMBER THAT?
- MM-HMM.

35:49.940 --> 35:52.829
- AND YOU KNOW HOW
YOU'VE BEEN WORKING WITH GABY

35:52.870 --> 35:55.839
AND SHE'S BEEN HELPING YOU LEARN
HOW TO PLAY WITH OTHER KIDS?

35:55.870 --> 35:57.838
- YEAH.

35:57.870 --> 36:00.703
- WELL, YOU'VE BEEN WORKING
SO HARD AT THESE THINGS

36:00.740 --> 36:02.947
BECAUSE YOU HAVE
ASPERGER'S SYNDROME.

36:02.980 --> 36:05.801
- YOU GUYS
ALREADY TOLD ME THAT.

36:05.850 --> 36:07.943
- RIGHT.
- YEAH.

36:07.990 --> 36:11.221
YEAH, WE DID, BUT WHAT
WE HAVEN'T HAD THE CHANCE TO DO

36:11.270 --> 36:13.886
IS TO TELL YOU
ABOUT ALL THE SPECIAL ABILITIES

36:13.930 --> 36:16.888
THAT PEOPLE
WITH ASPERGER'S HAVE...

36:16.930 --> 36:20.684
LIKE, FOR EXAMPLE,
YOU HAVE AN AMAZING MEMORY.

36:20.730 --> 36:24.962
AND YOU HAVE READ EVERY BOOK
EVER WRITTEN ABOUT PIRATES.

36:25.010 --> 36:27.387
AND YOU'RE PASSIONATE
ABOUT INSECTS.

36:27.420 --> 36:29.524
YOU'VE ALWAYS BEEN ABLE
TO MEMORIZE EVERY FACT

36:29.560 --> 36:31.380
ABOUT EVERY INSECT.

36:31.430 --> 36:34.638
AND THAT'S ALL
BECAUSE OF THE ASPERGER'S.

36:34.670 --> 36:35.830
- BUT THERE ARE SOME THINGS

36:35.880 --> 36:39.008
THAT ARE A LITTLE BIT MORE
CHALLENGING FOR YOU AS WELL.

36:39.050 --> 36:41.917
YOU KNOW, LIKE YOU HAD
TO LEARN TO REMEMBER

36:41.950 --> 36:44.646
TO LOOK INTO PEOPLE'S EYES
WHEN THEY'RE TALKING TO YOU

36:44.680 --> 36:46.671
OR TO SMILE AT SOMEONE

36:46.720 --> 36:49.575
WHEN YOU MEET THEM
FOR THE FIRST TIME

36:49.620 --> 36:53.329
OR TO STAY CALM IF SOMEBODY
HAS A DIFFERENT IDEA THAN YOU.

36:53.380 --> 36:55.416
AND, YOU KNOW,
SOMETIMES THESE THINGS

36:55.450 --> 36:57.896
COME A LITTLE BIT EASIER
TO OTHER KIDS,

36:57.930 --> 36:59.932
BUT YOU'VE REALLY HAD
TO WORK AT THEM.

36:59.970 --> 37:02.768
- AND WE KNOW HOW HARD
YOU'VE WORKED TO LEARN THEM.

37:02.800 --> 37:04.791
- YOU'RE A ROCK STAR.

37:07.050 --> 37:09.769
- WILL I ALWAYS HAVE IT?

37:14.920 --> 37:17.809
- YES.

37:17.850 --> 37:20.057
YEAH, YOU WILL ALWAYS HAVE
AN AMAZING MEMORY,

37:20.090 --> 37:21.569
AND YOU WILL ALWAYS
BE PASSIONATE

37:21.610 --> 37:23.498
ABOUT THE THINGS
THAT YOU'RE INTERESTED IN.

37:23.550 --> 37:26.064
AND THOSE SOCIAL SKILLS
THAT YOUR MOM MENTIONED,

37:26.100 --> 37:27.089
THOSE WILL ALWAYS BE THINGS

37:27.140 --> 37:29.279
THAT YOU JUST HAVE
TO REMIND YOURSELF ABOUT.

37:29.310 --> 37:31.039
- I ACTUALLY HAVE
A COUPLE OF BOOKS HERE

37:31.070 --> 37:34.938
DAD AND I HAVE BEEN READING
THAT TALK ABOUT AUTISM,

37:34.970 --> 37:37.552
AND THIS ONE HERE
WAS ACTUALLY WRITTEN BY A BOY

37:37.600 --> 37:38.931
WHO'S A COUPLE
YEARS OLDER THAN YOU

37:38.980 --> 37:41.005
WHO HAS ASPERGER'S SYNDROME.

37:41.050 --> 37:42.938
IT'S A REALLY INTERESTING BOOK,

37:42.980 --> 37:45.835
AND, UH, WE WILL SIT AND READ
THESE WITH YOU IF YOU WANT.

37:45.880 --> 37:47.871
OR IF YOU WANT TO READ THEM
BY YOURSELF

37:47.920 --> 37:49.706
AND ASK US QUESTIONS.

37:49.750 --> 37:51.741
WE'RE LEARNING TOGETHER,
ALL OF US.

37:51.780 --> 37:53.839
SO THIS IS ALL NEW FOR US TOO.

37:55.820 --> 37:57.572
- WE'RE PROUD OF YOU, MAX.

37:57.620 --> 37:59.884
- SO PROUD.
- EVERY DAY.

38:02.900 --> 38:04.925
- I WANT TO GO
PLAY BUG WARONLINE.

38:04.970 --> 38:07.063
- [chuckles]

38:07.110 --> 38:08.065
OKAY.

38:08.110 --> 38:09.828
- GO AHEAD.
- OKAY.

38:09.870 --> 38:12.100
- 30 MINUTES.
- 45.

38:12.150 --> 38:15.836
- 30.
- FINE.

38:15.870 --> 38:17.690
- I LOVE YOU.

38:23.990 --> 38:28.393
- WELL.
- I DIDN'T CRY.

38:28.440 --> 38:29.884
- YOU DID A GOOD JOB.

38:29.920 --> 38:33.048
- YOU DID SUCH A GOOD JOB.
I'M SO PROUD OF YOU.

38:33.100 --> 38:35.136
- YOU'RE A GOOD MOM,
GREAT MOM.

38:35.170 --> 38:37.718
- THANKS.

38:37.760 --> 38:40.376
I DIDN'T CRY.

38:40.420 --> 38:41.899
- ONE, TWO, THREE.

38:41.940 --> 38:44.898
- WHAT?

38:44.940 --> 38:46.862
BAM, OUT OF THE PLACE.

38:46.910 --> 38:48.764
- YOU KNOCKED ME OUT.

38:48.800 --> 38:50.142
I DON'T KNOW
WHY I PLAY WITH YOU.

38:50.180 --> 38:52.876
- SORRY.
TWO SORRIES.

38:52.910 --> 38:55.049
- I THINK YOU CHEAT.

38:55.090 --> 38:57.809
MM-HMM.

38:57.850 --> 38:59.738
- MOMMY SAYS
YOU NEED TO STAY HERE

38:59.780 --> 39:02.817
BECAUSE YOU'RE WORKING
ON THE BOAT.

39:02.850 --> 39:04.431
- UM...
[clears throat]

39:04.480 --> 39:06.926
YEAH.
THAT'S WHAT'S HAPPENING.

39:06.960 --> 39:10.088
- WHEN WILL YOU BE DONE
AND COME HOME?

39:10.140 --> 39:13.780
- WELL, IT'S GONNA BE
A WHILE, BUDDY.

39:13.830 --> 39:16.936
UH, I HAVE
A LOT OF WORK TO DO.

39:19.870 --> 39:21.929
- WHAT HAPPENED TO YOUR EYE?

39:21.980 --> 39:23.663
- WELL, WHAT DO YOU THINK
HAPPENED?

39:23.700 --> 39:26.908
- PUNCH, PUNCH, PUNCH.

39:26.950 --> 39:30.943
- I'M GONNA PUNCH, PUNCH YOU.

39:32.850 --> 39:38.959
- AND THE WHOLE WORLD
IS ON YOUR CASE

39:38.990 --> 39:42.403
I COULD OFFER YOU
A WARM EMBRACE

39:42.440 --> 39:44.886
- HI.

39:44.930 --> 39:46.966
- I NEED TO, UH...

39:47.000 --> 39:51.687
TELL YOU SOMETHING.

39:51.730 --> 39:54.039
- OKAY.

39:57.600 --> 40:00.068
- I WILL NEVER CHEAT ON YOU.

40:00.120 --> 40:01.838
- JOEL.

40:01.880 --> 40:05.464
- HONEY, YOU KNOW,
WE'VE BEEN THROUGH SO MUCH,

40:05.500 --> 40:07.559
AND...

40:07.610 --> 40:10.989
WE'RE GONNA GO THROUGH
SO MUCH MORE, YOU KNOW,

40:11.020 --> 40:12.908
GOOD AND BAD.

40:12.960 --> 40:16.088
WE'RE JUST--WE'RE GONNA GO
THROUGH EVERYTHING.

40:19.550 --> 40:22.201
AND I WILL NEVER...

40:22.240 --> 40:24.037
I WILL NEVER CHEAT ON YOU.

40:25.940 --> 40:29.103
- COME HERE.

40:29.150 --> 40:34.520
I'VE KNOWN IT
FROM THE MOMENT THAT WE MET

40:34.570 --> 40:36.709
NO DOUBT IN MY MIND

40:36.740 --> 40:39.538
THAT YOU BELONG

40:41.230 --> 40:47.783
I'D GO HUNGRY,
I GO BLACK AND BLUE

40:47.820 --> 40:53.850
I GO CRAWLING
DOWN THE AVENUE

40:53.890 --> 40:59.795
NO, THERE'S NOTHING
THAT I WOULDN'T DO

40:59.830 --> 41:04.073
TO MAKE YOU FEEL MY LOVE

41:16.880 --> 41:18.848
- "'HEARD THE NEWS?" HE SAID.

41:18.890 --> 41:20.846
"THERE'S NOTHING ELSE BEING
TALKED ABOUT

41:20.890 --> 41:23.029
"ALL ALONG THE RIVERBANK.

41:23.060 --> 41:26.268
"TOAD WENT UP TO TOWN
BY AN EARLY TRAIN THIS MORNING,

41:26.310 --> 41:30.963
AND HE'S ORDERED A VERY LARGE
AND VERY EXPENSIVE MOTOR CAR."'

41:31.000 --> 41:35.755
- THE STORMS ARE RAGING
ON THE ROLLING SEAS

41:35.800 --> 41:37.654
- MAX?

41:37.700 --> 41:43.559
- AND ON THE HIGHWAY
OF REGRET

41:43.600 --> 41:49.288
THE WINDS OF CHANGE
ARE BLOWING WILD AND FREE

41:49.330 --> 41:55.155
YOU AIN'T SEEN NOTHING
LIKE ME YET...

41:55.200 --> 41:57.748
- "THE MOLE HAD LONG WANTED

41:57.790 --> 41:59.337
"TO MAKE THE ACQUAINTANCE
OF THE BADGER.

41:59.370 --> 42:04.649
BUT WHENEVER HE MENTIONED
HIS WISH TO..."

42:04.690 --> 42:08.308
HE ALWAYS FOUND HIMSELF
PUT OFF."

42:08.350 --> 42:14.835
- GO TO THE ENDS
OF THE EARTH FOR YOU

42:14.870 --> 42:20.945
TO MAKE YOU FEEL MY LOVE

